<br />
Orange drops are already BoP and submitted to TLC (which make sense).<br />
Blue drops are free but usually they are crap.<br />
<br />
Making Yellow BoP will destroy our main source of income.<br />
<br />
Last week i did ToT and got a great plate helm on a lucky roll.<br />
I sold that helm for 40G (weeeeee !).<br />
<br />
With the new system, EVERY valuable (yellow) item will be BoP.<br />
<br />
There will be no &quot;item market&quot; since every single valuable loot (yellow) will be BoP.<br />
No 40G helms, just &quot;another T5 dust&quot; (probably a Resonating Crystal of Accuracy).<br />
<br />
<br />
I think putting restrictions on items is a good idea... But BoP is BRUTAL.<br />
No more twinks, no more cash items, no more Nothing.<br />
You just killed one of the best features of EQ... : Fungi Dual SoD CoF Iksar Monks<br />
<br />
BoE Yellows ? Why not they are &quot;good&quot; items putting a &quot;no-reuse&quot; makes sense.<br />
<br />
But BoP Yellows will destroy the entire market.<br />
You will only have 3 items on broker : Shitty Blues / Dusts / Crafted Stuff.<br />
<br />
Crafter stuff is BoE, and ranges from Blue to Yellow to Orange.<br />
<br />
So why BoP yellows ?<br />
