<br />
The change to Deconstruct is something LONG due.<br />
Adventurers were OUTSIDE the crafting cycle from day one.<br />
This was horrible, since we had control of nothing. Crafting was self-sufficient.<br />
<br />
There was no &quot;3-way trade&quot; or anything like that.<br />
With this change, there will be a 3 way trade.<br />
<br />
Harvesters control the flow of the Mats.<br />
Crafters control the combine.<br />
Adventurers control the dusts.<br />
<br />
Seeing a crafter getting a Sorcery/Striking/Pain dust from a WO and then<br />
telling you &quot;blow me and i MAY sell it for 1Plat&quot; was stupid.<br />
<br />
I am GLAD they chose to give adventurers control of the dust.<br />
This should had been done a LONG time ago, and exactly like WoW.<br />
Actually WoW's Disenchant 2.0 system should had been copied since day 1.
                  
