		<div id="post_message_1184874">
                  
                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Drkpl2</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">I do see this killing the cash flow of adventures, but this is not going to stop crafters from robbing us blind on their gear.  Yeah we will have their dusts, but that is going to sell cheap because of how much will now be out there.<br />
<br />
I mean I pick up anything but light armor, okay I decon it and get some gold for it.  There being soo much dusts out there, the crafters are going to be the only one buying them up, and the price will be cheap.  then they will crank up their prices on their gear............<br />
<br />
How does this help the econemy ?  Just puts the money back in the crafters again and the adventures having little money, and a lot of dust because no one will buy it all.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
After some more thought....<br />
<br />
Well I Think understand WHY they did it.  I just dont agree with it.<br />
<br />
Here's why I think they did it:<br />
<br />
Remember that Decon will result in dust OR MAT.<br />
<br />
This means we will be able to provie the dusts / mats to the crafters, and they will charge us a *service* fee for the final combine.<br />
<br />
This (in theory) drops the prices on crafted goods dramatically.  <br />
<br />
Realistically what are we as adventurer's using our money for.<br />
<br />
#1 To buy RARE items that are not on world loot tables (IE seskarlans bauble, ancient preserved pharaoh's bp, cinderskin tunic...ect) that are grossly overpiced (40-1p)<br />
<br />
#2 To buy Heroic crafted crystals / shards / dusts, and Heroic Harvestables, and to pay crafters for their combine's (boats, horseshoes, bags, armor, weapons, jewlery)<br />
<br />
#3 To buy fluff stuff like housing and horses, riftway shards, temp flying mounts, food, and repairs<br />
<br />
<br />
So what this does is only make us need large sums of money for buying fluff stuff.  The rest we must go out and adventure for.<br />
<br />
Now Why I dont agree with it.<br />
<br />
#1 I've met and made several friends passing gear down to other players.  Random casters i've run by and inspected would find a nice upgrade of armor in the mail the next day.  We keep in touch and either start to group up together or chat every once in a while about gear upgrades, spells armor game stuff.<br />
BOP on yellows means I can no longer have a chance at getting the items back, it also means that you cant do this.  Most blue items are sidegrades from your average low 20's - low 30's toon that would leap for joy at getting a &quot;nice&quot; yellow item.  I used to think getting a heroic or legendary at this level was near impossible.<br />
<br />
#2 World loot yellows are not of the same quality of mob loot table yellows.  I'd put these as a sidegrade from most BLUE items that are mob dropped and tradeable.  So there's no reason these should just be BOP too.  As my dad always said if you're going to do something dont half @$$ it.  Do it 100% or dont do it at all.  <br />
<br />
#3 Eq2's got a stable market economy, and you can buy some raid quality gear, some raid crafted gear, lots of legendary (vanguard's equiviant is heroic).  When you check the broker, you get a laundry list of things to wade through, and theres lots of gear choices.  Putting rares on BOP (soulbound) removes 90% of the adventuring armor off the broker.<br />
<br />
#4 this forces players to buy crafted goods for upgrades.  Really who the hell camps a mob for a yellow?  (unless its a lvl 50+ yellow like the ones i mentioned earlier)  from 40-50 I spent most my time camping mobs for HEROICS, I market sold the yellows, or gave them away.  I gave a lot away in fact.  So now the only way to get decent gear on the broker is through crafted.  Kind of makes it pointless to go out and camp a mob for anything because crafted is so good.  (people are lazy).
                  
		</div>
