		<div id="post_message_1184902">
                  
                  Yes Illusive, I fully understand the &quot;intent&quot; of these actions for BOP, I just do not think that the crafters are going to lower their prices at all.  I mean why would they ?  <br />
<br />
1- they will have an over abundance of dusts, crystals, whatever from all the adventures deconning everything they do not or can not use from a drop.<br />
<br />
2- as you already pointed out, they will be the ONLY source of a good upgrade for most of the population.  Yes some will go thru the steps of camping a name to get a good drop off them, but most will not.<br />
<br />
3- I am unaware of the pricing on the other servers, but on Tharridon it is thru the roof ( yes some of this will change with merger ) I mean unless it is thru someone I know, to get a T5 you are looking at about a plat at least after giving them all the resources needed.  True they will not be able to charge as much as they do now, but they will still take full advantage of taking as much as they can for most players.<br />
<br />
This is just the way I am looking at it, I too give out a lot of gear that I run across to lower level players that I run into.  And as you pointed out, most will jump out of their armor when you do ( lol more so maybe on a PVP where you are giving them things to maybe catch you with later ) <br />
<br />
I guess I could agree with the BOE going to all rares and higher, that would lower the number of things that get used and then sold, but that would still leave the mass number of farmers that sell them left and right on the broker.<br />
<br />
I sell a few things on the broker, most I hand out or send to a crafter I know for a favor down the road.  Yes, I agree that there is a huge amount of cash flowing thru the game, and most players should not be having lots of cash ( much over a plat ) but I guess I just do not see this as the fix.
                  
		</div>
