		<div id="post_message_1184913">
                  
                  my thoughts about gu#2:<br />
<br />
ok, I was stupid not to expect BOE on everything when they introduced it for crafted items. This is doing things in the wrong order. There are so much other urgent issues and BOE is not solving any problem I have, instead it creates inconvenience for me.<br />
<br />
I hope removing EE is helping the developers to get the engine straight because I’m not sure the removal is of any benefit for the players.<br />
<br />
I’m sure, rest experiences will help the player to focus on the right content. In few days from 1 to 50 and then the real game starts. In EQ2 they usually played around with the exp to prepare for an expansion.<br />
<br />
When I read diplomacy UI update I thought about managing decks with saving card combinations and easy switching between saved decks. Stupid me.<br />
<br />
How the big deconstruction change is going to work out, I will see. Anyway the change is not made because the player asked for it. It was a necessary for the BOx change.<br />
<br />
The item UI will really help me understand equipment. I never knew what all the procs or item effects actually really did from just seeing the name. This is the only thing I’m looking forward to.<br />
<br />
I did not understand one thing from the scrolling text chapter. I’m not reading the log when I’m in the middle of an encounter. I have no time for this. But I look at the log after a game session, it is so messed up that the parsing script has more code for exception handling than anything else. Every pars in a new environment adds additional lines and I’m still missing lots of the exception handling for classes I rarely play together with.<br />
<br />
And about your money concerns: I never farmed equipment for money. So I don’t have lots of money but I also don’t see why I would need lots of money in this game. Better equipment would improve my damage but the current content works well with the equipment I have. So what I’m looking for?
                  
		</div>
